</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1381,2020]" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1453,1479]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Head</emphasis>
subquadrate, white, with black 
<emphasis box="[628,676,1454,1479]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">eyes</emphasis>
near anterior margin. 
<emphasis box="[934,1062,1453,1479]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Antennulae</emphasis>
with two articles, antennae with three articles, without setae (
<figureCitation box="[470,557,1489,1515]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,387,1670]" captionTargetId="figure-108@5.[151,1436,381,1676]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Loki athanus n.sp., holotype female (UF18690) (A–F), paratype male (UF18690) (G–K): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; ur = uropods; pl = pleopod; pe1 = pereopod 1; pe2 = pereopod 2; pe3 = pereopod 3; eg = eggs); B, right antennula and antennae; C, right part of barbula; D, right maxilliped, external view; E, left oostegite 1, internal view; F, right pereopod 2; G, dorsal view; H, ventral view; I, right antennula and antenna; J, left pereopod 1; K, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A = 1 mm; B, D–F = 0.63 mm; C, G, H= 0.44 mm; I–K=0.13 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406607/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[578,670,1489,1515]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Barbula</emphasis>
with one falcate lateral projection on each side (
<figureCitation box="[1208,1295,1489,1515]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,387,1670]" captionTargetId="figure-108@5.[151,1436,381,1676]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Loki athanus n.sp., holotype female (UF18690) (A–F), paratype male (UF18690) (G–K): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; ur = uropods; pl = pleopod; pe1 = pereopod 1; pe2 = pereopod 2; pe3 = pereopod 3; eg = eggs); B, right antennula and antennae; C, right part of barbula; D, right maxilliped, external view; E, left oostegite 1, internal view; F, right pereopod 2; G, dorsal view; H, ventral view; I, right antennula and antenna; J, left pereopod 1; K, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A = 1 mm; B, D–F = 0.63 mm; C, G, H= 0.44 mm; I–K=0.13 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406607/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[1315,1436,1489,1515]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Maxilliped</emphasis>
without palp, and with short, blunt plectron (
<figureCitation box="[652,742,1525,1551]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,387,1670]" captionTargetId="figure-108@5.[151,1436,381,1676]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Loki athanus n.sp., holotype female (UF18690) (A–F), paratype male (UF18690) (G–K): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; ur = uropods; pl = pleopod; pe1 = pereopod 1; pe2 = pereopod 2; pe3 = pereopod 3; eg = eggs); B, right antennula and antennae; C, right part of barbula; D, right maxilliped, external view; E, left oostegite 1, internal view; F, right pereopod 2; G, dorsal view; H, ventral view; I, right antennula and antenna; J, left pereopod 1; K, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A = 1 mm; B, D–F = 0.63 mm; C, G, H= 0.44 mm; I–K=0.13 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406607/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1381,2020]" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">
<emphasis box="[199,279,1562,1587]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Pereon</emphasis>
yellow. First three pereomeres merged into ring encircling the head. Other pereomeres distinct on short side of the body but fused on long side (
<figureCitation box="[615,706,1597,1623]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,387,1670]" captionTargetId="figure-108@5.[151,1436,381,1676]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Loki athanus n.sp., holotype female (UF18690) (A–F), paratype male (UF18690) (G–K): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; ur = uropods; pl = pleopod; pe1 = pereopod 1; pe2 = pereopod 2; pe3 = pereopod 3; eg = eggs); B, right antennula and antennae; C, right part of barbula; D, right maxilliped, external view; E, left oostegite 1, internal view; F, right pereopod 2; G, dorsal view; H, ventral view; I, right antennula and antenna; J, left pereopod 1; K, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A = 1 mm; B, D–F = 0.63 mm; C, G, H= 0.44 mm; I–K=0.13 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406607/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Brood pouch pigmented, swollen, full of eggs, covering entire ventral surface of head and pereon. First oostegite with unadorned internal ridge, with broad notch along posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[246,333,1669,1695]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,387,1670]" captionTargetId="figure-108@5.[151,1436,381,1676]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Loki athanus n.sp., holotype female (UF18690) (A–F), paratype male (UF18690) (G–K): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; ur = uropods; pl = pleopod; pe1 = pereopod 1; pe2 = pereopod 2; pe3 = pereopod 3; eg = eggs); B, right antennula and antennae; C, right part of barbula; D, right maxilliped, external view; E, left oostegite 1, internal view; F, right pereopod 2; G, dorsal view; H, ventral view; I, right antennula and antenna; J, left pereopod 1; K, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A = 1 mm; B, D–F = 0.63 mm; C, G, H= 0.44 mm; I–K=0.13 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406607/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Fig. 3E</figureCitation>
). All 
<emphasis box="[395,511,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">pereopods</emphasis>
of similar size and shape (
<figureCitation box="[813,898,1669,1695]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,387,1670]" captionTargetId="figure-108@5.[151,1436,381,1676]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Loki athanus n.sp., holotype female (UF18690) (A–F), paratype male (UF18690) (G–K): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; ur = uropods; pl = pleopod; pe1 = pereopod 1; pe2 = pereopod 2; pe3 = pereopod 3; eg = eggs); B, right antennula and antennae; C, right part of barbula; D, right maxilliped, external view; E, left oostegite 1, internal view; F, right pereopod 2; G, dorsal view; H, ventral view; I, right antennula and antenna; J, left pereopod 1; K, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A = 1 mm; B, D–F = 0.63 mm; C, G, H= 0.44 mm; I–K=0.13 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406607/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
), with stout ischia and short, blunt dactyli. First two pairs of pereopods clustered near head; other five on short side in line along pereon, while on long side pereopod 3 is near middle of brood pouch, 4, 5 near posterolateral border of brood pouch, and 6, 7 near posterior end of brood pouch.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1381,2020]" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">
<emphasis box="[199,264,1813,1839]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Pleon</emphasis>
of five pleomeres (
<figureCitation box="[484,574,1813,1839]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,387,1670]" captionTargetId="figure-108@5.[151,1436,381,1676]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Loki athanus n.sp., holotype female (UF18690) (A–F), paratype male (UF18690) (G–K): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; ur = uropods; pl = pleopod; pe1 = pereopod 1; pe2 = pereopod 2; pe3 = pereopod 3; eg = eggs); B, right antennula and antennae; C, right part of barbula; D, right maxilliped, external view; E, left oostegite 1, internal view; F, right pereopod 2; G, dorsal view; H, ventral view; I, right antennula and antenna; J, left pereopod 1; K, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A = 1 mm; B, D–F = 0.63 mm; C, G, H= 0.44 mm; I–K=0.13 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406607/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
), first four produced into uniramous lateral plates, with uniramous pleopods, fifth without lateral plates, with divergent pair of uniramous uropods.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1381,2020]" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3028150304" collectionCode="UF" pageId="4" pageNumber="268" specimenCode="UF 18690" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="paratype">
<emphasis box="[199,364,1885,1911]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">
<typeStatus box="[199,302,1886,1911]" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Paratype</typeStatus>
male
</emphasis>
(
<specimenCode box="[380,498,1885,1912]" collectionCode="UF" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34858" name="Florida Museum of Natural History- Zoology, Paleontology and Paleobotany" pageId="4" pageNumber="268" type="Museum">UF 18690</specimenCode>
) length 
<quantity box="[591,681,1885,1912]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="268" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
, maximum width (across pereomere 1) 
<quantity box="[1132,1235,1885,1911]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="268" unit="mm" value="0.19">0.19 mm</quantity>
, head length 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="268" unit="mm" value="0.09">0.09 mm</quantity>
, head width 
<quantity box="[339,441,1921,1948]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="268" unit="mm" value="0.15">0.15 mm</quantity>
, pleonal length 
<quantity box="[619,719,1921,1947]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="268" unit="mm" value="0.12">0.12 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[734,859,1921,1947]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,387,1670]" captionTargetId="figure-108@5.[151,1436,381,1676]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Loki athanus n.sp., holotype female (UF18690) (A–F), paratype male (UF18690) (G–K): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; ur = uropods; pl = pleopod; pe1 = pereopod 1; pe2 = pereopod 2; pe3 = pereopod 3; eg = eggs); B, right antennula and antennae; C, right part of barbula; D, right maxilliped, external view; E, left oostegite 1, internal view; F, right pereopod 2; G, dorsal view; H, ventral view; I, right antennula and antenna; J, left pereopod 1; K, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A = 1 mm; B, D–F = 0.63 mm; C, G, H= 0.44 mm; I–K=0.13 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406607/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Fig. 3G, H</figureCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1381,2020]" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1957,1983]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Head</emphasis>
semicircular, with large black eyes near posterolateral margin (
<figureCitation box="[991,1083,1957,1983]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,387,1670]" captionTargetId="figure-108@5.[151,1436,381,1676]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Loki athanus n.sp., holotype female (UF18690) (A–F), paratype male (UF18690) (G–K): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; ur = uropods; pl = pleopod; pe1 = pereopod 1; pe2 = pereopod 2; pe3 = pereopod 3; eg = eggs); B, right antennula and antennae; C, right part of barbula; D, right maxilliped, external view; E, left oostegite 1, internal view; F, right pereopod 2; G, dorsal view; H, ventral view; I, right antennula and antenna; J, left pereopod 1; K, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A = 1 mm; B, D–F = 0.63 mm; C, G, H= 0.44 mm; I–K=0.13 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406607/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
). Antennae visible from dorsal view, antennulae and antennae with 3 and 5 articles respectively, terminal articles setose (
<figureCitation box="[1153,1231,1993,2019]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,387,1670]" captionTargetId="figure-108@5.[151,1436,381,1676]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Loki athanus n.sp., holotype female (UF18690) (A–F), paratype male (UF18690) (G–K): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; ur = uropods; pl = pleopod; pe1 = pereopod 1; pe2 = pereopod 2; pe3 = pereopod 3; eg = eggs); B, right antennula and antennae; C, right part of barbula; D, right maxilliped, external view; E, left oostegite 1, internal view; F, right pereopod 2; G, dorsal view; H, ventral view; I, right antennula and antenna; J, left pereopod 1; K, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A = 1 mm; B, D–F = 0.63 mm; C, G, H= 0.44 mm; I–K=0.13 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406607/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="268">Fig. 3I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis box="[199,279,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="269">Pereon</emphasis>
with first segment fused with head, two to seven distinct laterally, but slightly fused near midline (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,387,1670]" captionTargetId="figure-108@5.[151,1436,381,1676]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Loki athanus n.sp., holotype female (UF18690) (A–F), paratype male (UF18690) (G–K): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; ur = uropods; pl = pleopod; pe1 = pereopod 1; pe2 = pereopod 2; pe3 = pereopod 3; eg = eggs); B, right antennula and antennae; C, right part of barbula; D, right maxilliped, external view; E, left oostegite 1, internal view; F, right pereopod 2; G, dorsal view; H, ventral view; I, right antennula and antenna; J, left pereopod 1; K, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A = 1 mm; B, D–F = 0.63 mm; C, G, H= 0.44 mm; I–K=0.13 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406607/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="269">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
); with curved margins; first segment widest. Pair of pigmented lines extending from third to seventh pereomere (
<figureCitation box="[160,250,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,387,1670]" captionTargetId="figure-108@5.[151,1436,381,1676]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Loki athanus n.sp., holotype female (UF18690) (A–F), paratype male (UF18690) (G–K): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; ur = uropods; pl = pleopod; pe1 = pereopod 1; pe2 = pereopod 2; pe3 = pereopod 3; eg = eggs); B, right antennula and antennae; C, right part of barbula; D, right maxilliped, external view; E, left oostegite 1, internal view; F, right pereopod 2; G, dorsal view; H, ventral view; I, right antennula and antenna; J, left pereopod 1; K, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A = 1 mm; B, D–F = 0.63 mm; C, G, H= 0.44 mm; I–K=0.13 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406607/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="269">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
). All pereopods with short dactyli; first two pereopods slightly larger than others, but similar in structure (
<figureCitation box="[160,275,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,387,1670]" captionTargetId="figure-108@5.[151,1436,381,1676]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Loki athanus n.sp., holotype female (UF18690) (A–F), paratype male (UF18690) (G–K): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; ur = uropods; pl = pleopod; pe1 = pereopod 1; pe2 = pereopod 2; pe3 = pereopod 3; eg = eggs); B, right antennula and antennae; C, right part of barbula; D, right maxilliped, external view; E, left oostegite 1, internal view; F, right pereopod 2; G, dorsal view; H, ventral view; I, right antennula and antenna; J, left pereopod 1; K, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A = 1 mm; B, D–F = 0.63 mm; C, G, H= 0.44 mm; I–K=0.13 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406607/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="269">Fig. 3J, K</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,357]" box="[199,1399,295,321]" pageId="5" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis box="[199,264,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="269">Pleon</emphasis>
fused into triangular piece, narrower than last pereomere (
<figureCitation box="[921,1046,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1723]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,387,1670]" captionTargetId="figure-108@5.[151,1436,381,1676]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Loki athanus n.sp., holotype female (UF18690) (A–F), paratype male (UF18690) (G–K): A, dorsal view (lp = lateral plates; ur = uropods; pl = pleopod; pe1 = pereopod 1; pe2 = pereopod 2; pe3 = pereopod 3; eg = eggs); B, right antennula and antennae; C, right part of barbula; D, right maxilliped, external view; E, left oostegite 1, internal view; F, right pereopod 2; G, dorsal view; H, ventral view; I, right antennula and antenna; J, left pereopod 1; K, left pereopod 7. Scale bar: A = 1 mm; B, D–F = 0.63 mm; C, G, H= 0.44 mm; I–K=0.13 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406607/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="269">Fig. 3G, H</figureCitation>
). Pleopods and uropods absent.
</paragraph>
